CrashPlanRemote
By Andy Sayler
September 2015

A CrashPlanDesktop wrapper for headless/remote CrashPlan access.

Tested with CrashPlan 4.3, 4.4

Implements http://support.code42.com/CrashPlan/Latest/Configuring/Using_CrashPlan_On_A_Headless_Computer

Process:
1. Downloads CrashPlan install from remote machine
2. Downloads Auth info from remote machine
3. Sets up SSH port forwarding
4. Launches local CrashPlanDesktop process
5. Cleans up

Stores installs at ~/.crashplanremote/

Usage:

    ./CrashPlanRemote <SSH Connection String>

Example:

    ./CrashPlanRemote user@server.test.com
